    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-idr-te-lsp-distribution-16.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-idr-te-lsp-distribution-16.txt</link>
        <title>"Distribution of Traffic Engineering (TE) Policies and State using BGP-LS", Stefano Previdi, Ketan Talaulikar, Jie Dong, Mach Chen, Hannes Gredler, Jeff Tantsura</title>
        <dc:date>2021-10-22T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document describes a mechanism to collect the Traffic Engineering and Policy information that is locally available in a node and advertise it into BGP Link State (BGP-LS) updates.  Such information can be used by external components for path computation, re-optimization, service placement, network visualization, etc.</description>
    </item>
